#. Tag: title
#, no-c-format
msgid "Adding a Red Hat Enterprise Linux Host"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#, no-c-format
msgid "A Red Hat Enterprise Linux host is based on an standard installation of Red Hat Enterprise Linux."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#, no-c-format
msgid "Red Hat Enterprise Virtualization hosts are based on a customized disk image with just enough Red Hat Enterprise Linux for virtualization. They are approved rather than added."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#, no-c-format
msgid "To add a Red Hat Enterprise Linux host, provide some details about it. The Manager logs into the host to perform virtualization checks, install packages, create a network bridge and reboot the host. The process of adding a new host can take up to 10 minutes. The process can be followed in the host's details pane."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#, no-c-format
msgid "Click the <guilabel>Hosts</guilabel> tab. The <guilabel>Hosts</guilabel> tab displays a list of all hosts in the system."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#, no-c-format
msgid "Click the <guibutton>New</guibutton> button. The <guilabel>New Host</guilabel> dialog displays. It allows you to configure three aspects of your new host, each identified by a tab. The tabs are <guilabel>General</guilabel>, <guilabel>Power Management</guilabel>, and <guilabel>SPM</guilabel>."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#, no-c-format
msgid "Click the <guilabel>General</guilabel> tab to enter the general configuration details of your host. Only the <guilabel>General</guilabel> configuration details are mandatory."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#, no-c-format
msgid "If your host has a power management device, click the <guilabel>Power Management</guilabel> tab to configure it. This allows the Manager to perform lifecycle operations on your host, like turning it off and on."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#, no-c-format
msgid "Red Hat Enterprise Virtualization recommends power management. Power management enables the system to fence a troublesome host by using an additional interface to bypass the host operating system."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#, no-c-format
msgid "If the host is to be Highly Available, power management must be enabled and configured."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#, no-c-format
msgid "Click the <guilabel>SPM</guilabel> tab to configure the host's priority when the Manager is assigning role of Storage Pool Manager. This can usually be left at the default value."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#, no-c-format
msgid "Click the <guibutton>OK</guibutton> when you've entered all the necessary configuration details of your host."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: title
#, no-c-format
msgid "Result"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#, no-c-format
msgid "The new host displays in the list of hosts with a status of <literal>Installing</literal>. Once installation is complete, the status will update to <literal>Reboot</literal> and then <literal>Awaiting</literal>. The host must be activated for the status to change to <literal>Up</literal>."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#, no-c-format
msgid "View the progress of the host installation on the Details pane."
msgstr ""

